erely affected. As of last week, pork processing capacity has dropped 25 percent.""The Associated Press reports the U.S. Department of Agriculture expects beef to rise in price by between one to two percent, poultry by 1.5 percent and pork between two and three percent."SOURCES: Associated Presshttps://apnews.com/cb9fd324e9e3276dd56075a78223b7bb***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
