e black hole of HR 6819 exists peacefully with its stellar companions, and astronomers used the orbits of the two stars to infer that an object with four times the solar mass is in the system, which can only be a black hole."SOURCES: Astronomy and Physics, European Southern Observatoryhttps://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso2007/eso2007a.pdfhttps://www.eso.org/public/news/eso2007/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
